  <div class="first">
    <div class="trans">
    <article id="real-time-web-for-masses" class="vessel">
      <div class="in">
        <h2>Real-time Web for masses</h2>
        <p>
          What is real-time Web? <strong>It's a bi-directional communication between browsers
            and web applications</strong>, usually solved by implementing a <strong>WebSockets</strong> server.
          But WebSockets are complicated and hard to scale! You don't need to care
          about it anymore. WebRocket is a broker - a tie between a very efficient WebSockets
          server implementation and your backend apps. 
        </p>
        <p>
          WebRocket combines <strong>very efficient and scalable WebSockets server</strong> with internal
          messaging and asynchronous backend communication. The core system is written in <strong>Go
            programming language</strong> - a reliable and extremally fun language, which we believe
          will rock development of distributed apps in the nearest future.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
    </div>
  </div>

