        <h2>No language barrier</h2>
        <p>
          WebRocket backends can be implemented in <strong>any programming language</strong>, which
          means that you don't have to learn new languages or complicated technologies
          to use the power of WebSockets in your apps. You can spend your saved time on
          learning Klingon instead... :)
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
    </div>
  </div>

